Leonard Frey https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonard_Frey 0 Leonard Frey (September 4, 1938 – August 24, 1988) was an American actor. He is best remembered for his performance in the 1971 film Fiddler on the Roof, which earned him an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor nomination. Frey made his stage debut in an Off-Broadway production of Little Mary Sunshine and received a Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Play nomination for The National Health.
